The paper presents a method for reducing the treewidth of a graph while preserving its minimal $s-t$ separators up to a certain fixed size, which has applications in solving various graph problems in linear time for every fixed number of removed vertices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with graph algorithms and complexity, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with graph algorithms and optimization techniques.
